TITLE: Judge drops charges against Vermont deputy who was shot by police in chaotic upstate NY brawl
SUMMARY: Charges have been dropped against Vermont Deputy Vito Caselnova who was involved in an upstate New York shootout that ended with the police opening fire at Caselnova.

TITLE: Florida officer has 'Baywatch' moment, saving 2 swimmers in daring ocean rescue
SUMMARY: A Florida police officer sprang into action to save two people struggling in a dangerous rip current. Police say the two pulled from the water are expected to be okay.

TITLE: Denver police searching for female shooter who injured 5 outside Dierks Bentley’s Whiskey Row bar
SUMMARY: Denver Police are searching for a female shooter who allegedly opened fire Saturday night outside of the Dierks Bentley’s Whiskey Row bar, injuring five bystanders.

TITLE: Colorado moose charged woman, headbutted and stomped on her while she was walking her dog
SUMMARY: A woman who was walking her leashed dog on a trail in Boulder County, Colorado, was attacked by a moose, according to wildlife officials.

TITLE: Prosecutors seek life imprisonment for Brooklyn subway shooter
SUMMARY: Federal prosecutors are seeking life in prison for Frank James who injured 10 people last year when he opened fire on a subway train in Brooklyn, New York City.

TITLE: 15-year-old girl killed in Pennsylvania school van crash
SUMMARY: A Pennsylvania crash involving a school van and a sedan has left five passengers injured, including two critically wounded adults. A 15-year-old girl also died from the collision.

TITLE: Murder-suicide at a Walmart in Hiram, Georgia, leaves 2 dead: police
SUMMARY: Two "younger people" are dead following a shooting at a Walmart Super Center in Hiram, Georgia, said Hiram Police Chief Mike Turner. The shooting is believed to be a murder-suicide.

TITLE: Missing F-35 jet was 'almost going inverted' before crash, witness says
SUMMARY: A witness in South Carolina says a military jet believed to have crashed in Williamsburg County on Sunday was flying nearly “inverted" before the moment of impact.

TITLE: Los Angeles woman robbed at gunpoint after suspect follows her into parking garage, video shows
SUMMARY: Police in Los Angeles are looking for two suspects after a woman was robbed at gunpoint in a parking garage in the exclusive Hancock Park neighborhood.

TITLE: Pennsylvania prison announces major change after convicted killer Cavalcante’s brazen escape
SUMMARY: A prison in Chester County, Pennsylvania, will make several security updates after convicted murderer Danelo Cavalcante escaped by scaling the walls, sparking a two-week long manhunt.

TITLE: Texas Gov. orders razor wire reinstalled at border, actor has message for Dems and more top headlines
SUMMARY: Texas Gov. orders razor wire reinstalled at border, actor has message for Dems and more top headlines

TITLE: Federal judge, 96, barred from hearing cases after panel claims lack of mental fitness: 'Baseless allegations'
SUMMARY: Judge Pauline Newman, the oldest sitting federal judge in America at 96 years old, was barred from hearing cases after a judicial panel claimed she is not mentally fit enough to serve.

TITLE: Minnesota man accused of using college dorm as torture den menaced ex with online messages: authorities
SUMMARY: A 19-year-old accused of holding his girlfriend captive and torturing her for days allegedly sent creepy messages to an ex-lover after she obtained a restraining order against him.

TITLE: Suspected robber who allegedly pistol-whipped store clerk stopped in his tracks by armed good Samaritan: cops
SUMMARY: Fort Lauderdale Police arrested Nicolas Richard Lee Deas after he allegedly pistol-whipped a Family Dollar employee and tried to steal cash before an armed witness intervened.

TITLE: Alex Murdaugh to plead guilty to financial crimes as alleged cohort makes stunning claim
SUMMARY: Disgraced attorney Alex Murdaugh will plead guilty Thursday to the theft of more than $9 million as his alleged cohort in a botched assisted suicide plot makes bombshell claim.

TITLE: California murderer who shot deputy, killed chaplain at age 24 granted 'youth offender' parole
SUMMARY: A California murderer who shot out a deputy's eye and killed a volunteer chaplain in 1994 has been granted parole years earlier than originally expected.

TITLE: Texas churchgoers get 'shotgun sermon' cooked up by chatbot
SUMMARY: The Violet Crown City Church in Austin, Texas decided to attempt a service that was generated entirely by the artificial intelligence application ChatGPT on Sunday,

TITLE: Human leg found sticking out of TD Bank dumpster in Queens, police investigating
SUMMARY: The New York Police Department responded to an anonymous call reporting that a foot was sticking out of a dumpster at a TD Bank in Queens.

TITLE: Indiana murder suspect accidentally released, police kept quiet for 6 days
SUMMARY: Indiana police kept the accidental release of a murder suspect for six days for a "tactical advantage."

TITLE: Florida women outside Coyote Ugly bar seen tossing baby around 'like a toy' moments before fight breaks out
SUMMARY: Surveillance video from a recreational cannabis store in Daytona Beach, Florida, captured a confrontation after two women allegedly tossed a baby around.

TITLE: Los Angeles DA George Gascon announces next steps after deputy's ambush killing
SUMMARY: George Gascon announced murder charges and three special circumstance charges in the ambush killing of a Los Angeles Sheriff's deputy on Sept. 16.

TITLE: Florida couple allegedly performed sex acts on children, face life in prison
SUMMARY: A Florida couple was arrested earlier this month for capital sexual battery after allegedly possessing, transmitting and producing child sexual abuse materials.

TITLE: Texas hurricane relief program workers robbed in 6 'brazen incidents' in recent months: 'Unacceptable'
SUMMARY: Construction workers in Texas working to help residents recover from 2017's Hurricane Harvey have been the victims of a number of armed robberies in recent months.

TITLE: Texas gang member gets life without parole for killing 11-year-old boy while free on bond for capital murder
SUMMARY: A Houston, Texasm, man who is a known gang member, was sentenced to life without parole after being convicted of killing an 11-year-old boy and his stepfather in October 2020.

TITLE: Man celebrating Florida's new open-carry law by firing rifle into the air faces multiple charges
SUMMARY: A South Florida man who was shot by police while firing a rifle into the air in celebration of Florida's new open-carry gun law has been formally incarcerated.
